@startuml
title D01 - High-Level Platform Structure
caption Overall problem/result flow across client, host, interface, and MCU-based Ising platform.

left to right direction

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam wrapWidth 180
skinparam maxMessageSize 120

skinparam node {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F8F8F8
}

skinparam component {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<Ready>> #DFF2BF
  BackgroundColor<<NeedsExpansion>> #FFF2B2
  BackgroundColor<<Investigative>> #BDE5F8
  BackgroundColor<<External>> #E0E0E0
}

skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor<<Host>> #E8F0FE
  BackgroundColor<<Interface>> #FFF7E6
  BackgroundColor<<Platform>> #EAF7EA
}

actor "Client / User\nResearcher, operator,\nor external program" as Client

node "Host System\nPC / Server / SBC" as Host <<Host>> {
  component "Host Control Software\n\nResponsibilities:\n- accept problem request\n- prepare experiment/job\n- encode platform input\n- collect and decode output\n- present results" as HostSW <<NeedsExpansion>>
}

node "Communication / Backend Interface\nLogical boundary or dedicated bridge device" as Interface <<Interface>> {
  component "Transport Adapter\nUSB / UART / SPI / WiFi / Ethernet / etc." as Transport <<NeedsExpansion>>
  component "Protocol / Backend Adapter\nHost-facing API ↔ platform-specific protocol" as Protocol <<NeedsExpansion>>
}

node "MCU Ising Platform\nMicrocontroller-based backend" as Platform <<Platform>> {
  component "Platform Firmware\n\nResponsibilities:\n- receive input job\n- configure solver\n- manage execution\n- return status/results" as Firmware <<NeedsExpansion>>

  component "Ising Computation Engine\n\nResponsibilities:\n- perform update steps\n- evaluate state/energy\n- produce solution candidate" as Solver <<Investigative>>
}

Client --> HostSW : 1. pose problem\nproblem instance, parameters,\nconstraints, run request

HostSW --> Transport : 2. send encoded input job\nbackend-independent or semi-portable form

Transport --> Protocol : 3. frame / transport / relay
Protocol --> Firmware : 4. platform-specific input\ncommands, data, configuration

Firmware --> Solver : 5. execute Ising computation
Solver --> Firmware : 6. computed output\nstate, energy, diagnostics

Firmware --> Protocol : 7. platform-specific output
Protocol --> Transport : 8. decode / translate / relay
Transport --> HostSW : 9. result package\nsolution, metrics, logs

HostSW --> Client : 10. present output\nsolution, status, analysis

note bottom of Interface
  The interface is intentionally shown as a separate architectural region.

  It may be:
  - only a logical protocol layer,
  - a USB/UART/SPI bridge,
  - a WiFi/Bluetooth communication module,
  - a backend adapter for FPGA or other accelerators,
  - or a device that participates in computation.

  This region should be expanded later.
end note

note bottom of Platform
  The MCU platform is the first concrete backend.

  Future diagrams should expand:
  - firmware module structure,
  - solver control flow,
  - memory layout,
  - host/platform command protocol,
  - computation behavior.
end note

legend right
  |= Visual status |= Meaning |
  | <back:#DFF2BF>Ready</back> | Stable enough for implementation |
  | <back:#FFF2B2>NeedsExpansion</back> | Requires lower-level diagram/spec |
  | <back:#BDE5F8>Investigative</back> | Design/research question remains open |
  | <back:#E0E0E0>External</back> | External dependency or tool |
endlegend

@enduml
